stories.title: West Indies v Zimbabwe
stories.subTitle: LG Abans Triangular Series, match 2
stories.summary: At Sinhalese Sports Club, Colombo, December 9

stories.title: Hooper admits to being disturbed after latest West Indian failure
stories.summary:
An increasingly despondent West Indies captain Carl Hooper admitted to being
disturbed by his sides continued poor performance in Sri Lanka, as they
slipped to a four-wicket defeat against Zimbabwe in the second game of the
LG Abans triangular series

stories.title: Zimbabwe clinch four-wicket victory in nervy encounter
stories.summary:
Zimbabwe successfully recovered from their chastening 38 all out on Saturday
to defeat a West Indies side that looks ill at ease after a spate of
injuries, disciplinary problems and a three-Test drumming by Sri Lanka
